CSS Locator:
-CSS doesn't allow you to access elements using TEXT.

Attribute - tagname[attribute='value']

Shortcuts:
- ID = tagname#value
- Class = tagname.value - If there is a space in the class you replace the space with a dot
- Contains = tagname[attribute*='value'] - Whenever an attribute has digits or spaces we can use it to avoid locator getting redundant
- Starts-with = tagname[attribute^='value']
- Ends-with = tagname[attribute$='value']

Radio Buttons:
- You can only select one option.
- isSelected() -> if the element is selected or not = boolean
- isEnabled() -> if the element is active or not = boolean
- isDisplayed() -> if the element is visible on screen or not = boolean

